text: Stray Kids, also known as SKZ, is a South Korean boy group from JYP Entertainment. They are an eight-member band producing Korean music. Their members were selected through a reality show by the same name, made by JYP Entertainment. They debuted as nine members on 25th of March 2018 with their debut album I Am NOT. Their latest album is GIANT, with the title song being of the same name. The eight current members are Bahng Christopher Chan (Bang Chan), Lee Min-ho (Lee Know), Seo Changbin (Changbin), Hwang Hyunjin (Hyunjin), Han Jisung (HAN), Lee Felix (Felix), Kim Seungmin (Seungmin), and Yang Jeongin (I.N). Former member Kim Woojin left the band in 2019 for personal reasons.
